info.title: Birdeye Data Services APIs
info.description:
To utilize the Birdeye Data Services APIs, an API key is required for authentication. You can obtain an API key by signing up for a bds.birdeye.so account and generating an API key in your account settings. Include this API key in the headers of your API requests for authentication.

Here's a step-by-step guide on how to obtain an API key: [Birdeye Data Services Authentication and API Keys](https://docs.birdeye.so/docs/authentication-api-keys)

parameters.description: Indicate whether to use padding on empty candles. Default: false

parameters.name: outlier
